@@TJvTreeViewCheckBoxOptions
Summary
  Class used to store checkbox options in a TJvCheckBoxTreeView.
Description
  The TJvTreeViewCheckBoxOptions class is the class used to store checkbox option settings in the
  TJvCheckTreeView components CheckBoxOptions property. Since this property is a class, it is
  displayed as a nested property set in the Object Inspector. An instance of this class is created
  automatically by the treeview. Do not create instances of this class yourself.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvTreeViewCheckBoxOptions.CascadeLevels
Summary
  Specifies the number of levels a toggle propagates.
Description
  \Read CascadeLevels to determine how many levels a toggle of a node propagates. If this property is
  0, no propagation takes place, if it is 1, toggling a node also toggles all checkbox node on the
  next sublevel.
  To toggle all subnodes regardless of depth, set CascadeLevels to -1.
See Also
  TJvTreeViewCheckBoxOptions.CascadeOptions

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvTreeViewCheckBoxOptions.CascadeOptions
Summary
  Specifies how toggles are propagated for checkbox nodes.
Description
  Use CascadeOptions to specify how checking/unchecking a checkbox node is propagated.
See Also
  TJvTreeViewCheckBoxOptions.CascadeLevels

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvTreeViewCheckBoxOptions.CheckBoxCheckedIndex
